) strongly reduced, with four podomeres, with a high, regularly rounded, outer coxal lobe; coxa with an apical setiferous spine; leg-pair 18 (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Hyleoglomeris alba Nguyen, Kuroda &amp; Eguchi, sp. nov., holotype A leg-pair 17 B leg 18 C left telopod, anterior view D subposterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1108.85423.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/705331" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">9B</figureCitation>
